1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

2
00:00:08,509 --> 00:00:11,645
I can't stand working
for Choi Ki-young anymore.

3
00:00:11,712 --> 00:00:13,881
That has nothing to do with us!

4
00:00:13,947 --> 00:00:15,182
Go to another company...

5
00:00:17,117 --> 00:00:18,485
Let's hear the details.

6
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:22,523
As I promised Mr. Choi,
TORINNER achieved first place

7
00:00:22,890 --> 00:00:24,391
in the debut song ranking.

8
00:00:24,791 --> 00:00:28,328
But he said their sales amount
doesn't justify the expenses

9
00:00:29,229 --> 00:00:30,330
and that's akin to a betrayal.

10
00:00:30,664 --> 00:00:31,698
No way...

11
00:00:31,765 --> 00:00:34,301
So you got fired for overspending.

12
00:00:34,368 --> 00:00:35,936
Just shut up and listen.

13
00:00:36,270 --> 00:00:39,039
I understand
he's stressed out as the CEO

14
00:00:39,573 --> 00:00:44,278
but he calls me incapable
and useless every day.

15
00:00:44,344 --> 00:00:45,379
That's so mean!

16
00:00:45,445 --> 00:00:49,950
Like I said,
it's none of our agency's business.

17
00:00:50,017 --> 00:00:52,319
And like I said,
just shut up and listen.

18
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:56,657
I've devoted my entire life
to producing artists.

19
00:00:57,524 --> 00:00:59,426
This job is the only thing I have.

20
00:01:00,327 --> 00:01:04,031
But Choi Ki-young has influence
all over this industry

21
00:01:05,198 --> 00:01:08,402
so I can only come here
to escape from him.

22
00:01:08,502 --> 00:01:12,573
True, he does hate our guts.
Clever thinking!

23
00:01:12,639 --> 00:01:15,475
How is that clever thinking, Minase?

24
00:01:15,542 --> 00:01:19,179
Have you forgotten all the trouble
this woman has given us?

25
00:01:19,246 --> 00:01:20,247
That's true!

26
00:01:20,314 --> 00:01:23,283
Besides, this woman stole
the TORINNER members from us

27
00:01:23,350 --> 00:01:25,052
and presented them to Choi Ki-young.

28
00:01:25,118 --> 00:01:27,621
Now that NAZE's career is
starting to take off smoothly

29
00:01:27,688 --> 00:01:29,623
this traitor wants to come back here?

30
00:01:29,923 --> 00:01:31,024
No way!

31
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:32,092
That makes sense.

32
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:41,435
I am very sorry.

33
00:01:43,837 --> 00:01:44,838
What?

34
00:01:44,905 --> 00:01:48,041
Please let me work with you again.

35
00:01:49,176 --> 00:01:50,177
Wait...

36
00:01:50,243 --> 00:01:53,280
But, we already have Mr. Azuma
as our producer--

37
00:01:53,347 --> 00:01:54,615
Okay. Let's do it together.

38
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:57,184
She's the best person
we could ever hope for

39
00:01:57,250 --> 00:01:58,852
if we want to help
those bumbling fools get better.

40
00:01:58,919 --> 00:02:01,555
Wait! Do you have no dignity?

41
00:02:01,622 --> 00:02:04,091
Training NAZE properly is my dignity.

42
00:02:04,157 --> 00:02:07,160
NAZE's current goal is to win
the Best New Artist Award at MAMA

43
00:02:07,227 --> 00:02:09,863
the music festival that is
garnering worldwide attention.

44
00:02:09,930 --> 00:02:14,401
So, the next song we release must
beat TORINNER and get first place.

45
00:02:14,468 --> 00:02:16,303
Ms. Park was the one
who trained TORINNER

46
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:20,407
so her social network and strategy
will be useful, don't you agree?

47
00:02:20,474 --> 00:02:22,409
You're right. This is
a dream collaboration.

48
00:02:22,476 --> 00:02:23,877
Hey, Nam. Tell me how you feel.

49
00:02:23,944 --> 00:02:24,945
I'm pissed off.

50
00:02:25,012 --> 00:02:26,013
Okay, it's decided.

51
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,949
Are you okay with this, Ms. Nam?

52
00:02:29,016 --> 00:02:30,417
I'm not okay!

53
00:02:31,518 --> 00:02:34,154
But I have no other choice.

54
00:02:34,221 --> 00:02:38,158
Feel free to give us any suggestions.
I look forward to working with you.

55
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:46,767
I look forward to working
with you, Mr. Azuma.

56
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:47,834
Good.

57
00:02:57,811 --> 00:03:00,814
Ms. Park Ji-soo will join
our team starting today.

58
00:03:00,881 --> 00:03:01,882
A round of applause.

59
00:03:01,948 --> 00:03:03,150
What? She's joining us?

60
00:03:03,216 --> 00:03:06,787
Mr. Azuma and I will turn you
into top stars together.

61
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:08,155
I look forward to working with you.

62
00:03:09,556 --> 00:03:11,558
"Together"?

63
00:03:11,658 --> 00:03:14,861
How about that? This is the birth
of the strongest duo!

64
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:22,135
Today, we're holding
a welcome party for Ms. Park.

65
00:03:22,202 --> 00:03:24,471
- Yay!
- Yay!

66
00:03:25,172 --> 00:03:26,173
What's this?

67
00:03:26,239 --> 00:03:29,409
Yaminabe, the only dish
Mr. Azuma is good at making.

68
00:03:29,476 --> 00:03:32,612
You're supposed to eat it
in a dark room, though.

69
00:03:32,679 --> 00:03:34,147
Japanese people sure are weird.

70
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:36,616
Most Japanese people don't even
know about something this obscure.

71
00:03:36,683 --> 00:03:39,052
Hey, that's rude to your producer.

72
00:03:39,119 --> 00:03:40,954
Today's hot pot tastes good, too.

73
00:03:41,021 --> 00:03:42,222
Okay, let's eat.

74
00:03:47,694 --> 00:03:50,330
You know, you don't have
to force yourselfto eat.

75
00:03:50,397 --> 00:03:52,265
Shut up.

76
00:04:03,176 --> 00:04:06,446
Wait a minute. It's delicious.

77
00:04:06,513 --> 00:04:08,548
Right?

78
00:04:08,615 --> 00:04:09,916
Okay. Dig in, everyone!

79
00:04:09,983 --> 00:04:12,919
- Yes. Let's eat!
- Yes. Let's eat!

80
00:04:12,986 --> 00:04:14,221
It looks delicious!

81
00:04:14,287 --> 00:04:15,589
It looks delicious!

82
00:04:17,591 --> 00:04:20,694
He never served me food before.

83
00:04:20,761 --> 00:04:23,864
Mr. Azuma,
do you cook for them yourself?

84
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:27,067
Occasionally. It tastes different
every time, though.

85
00:04:27,834 --> 00:04:29,736
Do-hyeok, eat your veggies!

86
00:04:29,803 --> 00:04:31,304
No, I'm good.

87
00:04:31,371 --> 00:04:34,674
- Eat it!
- Eat it! It's good for your health.

88
00:04:34,741 --> 00:04:36,543
You lied to me.

89
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:38,779
Incompetent people deserve to die.
You're worse than leftovers.

90
00:04:38,845 --> 00:04:40,213
I'm not complimenting you.

91
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,448
Get out!

92
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:45,051
- Eat!
- Eat more!

93
00:04:47,587 --> 00:04:49,389
- Eat!
- Hurry up!

94
00:04:49,456 --> 00:04:50,991
Wow!

95
00:04:51,057 --> 00:04:54,294
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

96
00:04:57,831 --> 00:04:59,432
It's warm.

97
00:05:01,168 --> 00:05:02,702
Sure is. It's hot pot, after all.

98
00:05:04,938 --> 00:05:06,006
Right.

99
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:13,346
What? Do you guys sleep here?

100
00:05:13,413 --> 00:05:15,081
Yes, it's the only room.

101
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:17,684
We sleep next to each other
like fish in the market.

102
00:05:17,751 --> 00:05:20,353
You can leave
if you don't like it, jerk!

103
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:22,956
- Nice catch!
- Mr. Azuma, do you sleep here too?

104
00:05:23,023 --> 00:05:27,594
These aliens have disrupted
the peaceful life of an innocent man.

105
00:05:27,661 --> 00:05:29,596
You feel lonely living alone.

106
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:32,098
I don't feel lonely.

107
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:34,801
Hey, stop playing!
Go and take a bath now.

108
00:05:34,868 --> 00:05:36,036
- Yes!
- Yes!

109
00:05:36,102 --> 00:05:38,738
I told you to use the rag
when you wipe!

110
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:42,008
It's okay. I can use this.

111
00:05:42,576 --> 00:05:44,778
Mr. Azuma is a strange person.

112
00:05:44,845 --> 00:05:46,646
Look who's talking.

113
00:05:46,713 --> 00:05:48,181
I agree, he's quite unusual.

114
00:05:48,248 --> 00:05:50,317
I'm very interested now.

115
00:05:50,383 --> 00:05:53,253
What? Is that...

116
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:54,754
What kind of interest
are you talking about?

117
00:05:54,821 --> 00:05:56,723
My interest in him
as an individual, of course.

118
00:05:58,425 --> 00:06:00,660
I'm leaving first.
We have an early day tomorrow.

119
00:06:02,295 --> 00:06:04,164
What's with her all of a sudden?

120
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:07,701
Or rather, I should say he's
an interesting person to study.

121
00:06:12,839 --> 00:06:16,877
Is Ms. Park serious
about coming back to us?

122
00:06:17,244 --> 00:06:18,678
Of course she's not.

123
00:06:18,979 --> 00:06:20,847
She must be plotting something.

124
00:06:25,085 --> 00:06:26,319
What's wrong, Yuya?

125
00:06:26,620 --> 00:06:27,621
It's nothing.

126
00:06:27,687 --> 00:06:29,890
Just that I haven't been able
to get a hold of Ryo for days.

127
00:06:30,257 --> 00:06:33,827
What? Ryo isn't calling back?
That's weird.

128
00:06:33,894 --> 00:06:37,564
TORINNER must be so busy
since they're superstars.

129
00:06:38,932 --> 00:06:40,500
Yeon-woo, are you okay?

130
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,402
Who said you could help him?

131
00:06:43,637 --> 00:06:45,705
Is that your limit already?

132
00:06:46,339 --> 00:06:47,807
That guy who just fell...

133
00:06:48,275 --> 00:06:49,910
I don't know his name

134
00:06:50,543 --> 00:06:52,145
but he's a member of TORINNER, right?

135
00:06:54,147 --> 00:06:55,148
Are you okay?

136
00:06:58,485 --> 00:06:59,586
Mr. Choi.

137
00:07:00,086 --> 00:07:01,087
As you instructed

138
00:07:01,154 --> 00:07:04,057
we've been having lessons
since this morning without a break.

139
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:07,794
Could you please let us
have a short break?

140
00:07:11,031 --> 00:07:13,199
I haven't taken a break either.

141
00:07:14,401 --> 00:07:18,571
Now that Ms. Park is gone,
I'm responsible for you guys.

142
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:22,475
If you feel that as strongly as I do,
you wouldn't have fallen.

143
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:24,444
Continue.

144
00:07:24,511 --> 00:07:26,813
- Hey, let's do it.
- Yes.

145
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:28,915
Five, six, seven, eight.

146
00:07:28,982 --> 00:07:31,117
One, two, three, four...

147
00:07:31,184 --> 00:07:32,352
Do-hyeok!

148
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:34,254
You got it wrong again!

149
00:07:34,321 --> 00:07:36,756
- What?
- Why?

150
00:07:36,823 --> 00:07:38,692
Get your act together!

151
00:07:40,226 --> 00:07:41,761
Once more!

152
00:07:41,828 --> 00:07:42,929
This is it.

153
00:07:43,096 --> 00:07:44,097
What?

154
00:07:44,164 --> 00:07:47,200
They're close, cute, and innocent.

155
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:49,402
Oh, that?

156
00:07:49,736 --> 00:07:51,404
That is the team's strength...

157
00:07:52,572 --> 00:07:53,573
as well as their obstacle.

158
00:07:54,307 --> 00:07:55,475
Obstacle?

159
00:07:56,843 --> 00:07:58,144
Let's have a meeting.

160
00:07:59,879 --> 00:08:02,849
NAZE's strength is that
they support each other as friends

161
00:08:02,916 --> 00:08:03,917
and they're earnest.

162
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:05,352
They exude boyish innocence...

163
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:09,122
They're honest and very good boys.

164
00:08:09,189 --> 00:08:11,791
But they'll never beat TORINNER
if that's all they have.

165
00:08:11,858 --> 00:08:14,227
What? What did you say?

166
00:08:14,294 --> 00:08:16,696
- Ms. Park is right.
- What?

167
00:08:16,896 --> 00:08:18,465
It's nice to show respect
out of friendship

168
00:08:18,531 --> 00:08:21,468
but fans will find it
too predictable.

169
00:08:21,968 --> 00:08:23,003
She has a point.

170
00:08:23,069 --> 00:08:24,871
It's good enough to select songs
matching the group's concept

171
00:08:24,938 --> 00:08:26,706
before they find their own identity.

172
00:08:26,806 --> 00:08:28,541
But if we want to reach out
to a wider audience

173
00:08:28,608 --> 00:08:31,011
it would make sense to expand their
repertoire in a different direction.

174
00:08:31,077 --> 00:08:32,245
Did I get that right?

175
00:08:32,312 --> 00:08:34,714
But our members are fixed.

176
00:08:35,482 --> 00:08:37,350
This isn't easy to achieve.

177
00:08:37,417 --> 00:08:39,386
They're losers if they can't do it.

178
00:08:39,819 --> 00:08:41,287
Watch what you're saying!

179
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:42,889
If they don't change
or challenge themselves

180
00:08:42,956 --> 00:08:44,391
and stay in their comfort zone

181
00:08:44,457 --> 00:08:46,059
people will grow tired of them soon.

182
00:08:46,126 --> 00:08:47,460
I'm impressed, Ms. Park.

183
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:49,462
Thank you.

184
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:53,099
What do you think
about specific ideas like these?

185
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:55,001
You work fast.

186
00:08:55,735 --> 00:08:58,738
I summarized the concepts
and visual images of new songs

187
00:08:58,805 --> 00:09:00,607
by their patterns.

188
00:09:01,307 --> 00:09:04,210
Overall, I think the ideas
you gave were great, Ms. Park.

189
00:09:04,277 --> 00:09:07,947
I can't come up with ideas anyway.

190
00:09:08,348 --> 00:09:09,382
That reminds me.

191
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:12,585
What's the matter, Mr. Azuma?

192
00:09:12,752 --> 00:09:17,157
Ms. Park says maybe we can try
adding Korean zucchini to Yaminabe.

193
00:09:17,590 --> 00:09:18,892
Go do some grocery shopping.

194
00:09:20,593 --> 00:09:22,729
So, the costumes...

195
00:09:22,796 --> 00:09:25,131
Darn you!

196
00:09:25,732 --> 00:09:29,202
Why do I have
to buy groceries and cook?

197
00:09:29,269 --> 00:09:30,670
I'm not your domestic helper.

198
00:09:30,737 --> 00:09:32,605
Minase, are you angry?

199
00:09:32,672 --> 00:09:35,108
You're emanating
a very negative aura.

200
00:09:35,175 --> 00:09:39,412
Sorry. I couldn't help
saying my thoughts out loud.

201
00:09:39,479 --> 00:09:40,947
We'll help you cook.

202
00:09:41,014 --> 00:09:42,182
Thank you.

203
00:09:43,216 --> 00:09:44,984
But Minase, you're so nice.

204
00:09:45,685 --> 00:09:46,986
You'll make a good wife.

205
00:09:47,187 --> 00:09:49,289
Hey, I agree!

206
00:09:49,355 --> 00:09:52,225
What? Why are you saying that
out of the blue?

207
00:09:52,292 --> 00:09:53,927
Your only flaw is that
you can't cook.

208
00:09:53,993 --> 00:09:54,994
Shut up.

209
00:09:55,695 --> 00:09:58,465
Minase, do you have a boyfriend?

210
00:09:58,531 --> 00:09:59,799
No, no, I don't.

211
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:01,301
But...

212
00:10:02,802 --> 00:10:07,474
There is... someone I like.

213
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:10,110
- What?
- What?

214
00:10:10,176 --> 00:10:11,211
What is he like?

215
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:14,414
Well, he's usually brusque

216
00:10:14,781 --> 00:10:17,350
but he's actually
a romantic at heart.

217
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:20,620
He's working hard
towards pursuing his dream.

218
00:10:20,687 --> 00:10:23,223
- Wow!
- Wow! Isn't that nice?

219
00:10:23,289 --> 00:10:26,526
- Are you going to ask him out?
- No. Somehow...

220
00:10:27,093 --> 00:10:30,697
I don't think he's interested in me

221
00:10:30,763 --> 00:10:33,166
and I think he's in love
with someone else.

222
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:34,834
It's over if you give up!

223
00:10:34,901 --> 00:10:35,935
We'll root for you!

224
00:10:36,002 --> 00:10:37,837
Where would be a good place
for a date?

225
00:10:37,904 --> 00:10:39,672
A romantic place would be nice.

226
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:41,474
Yeah, I agree.

227
00:10:41,541 --> 00:10:43,276
- The Sapporo Snow Festival!
- Too soon for a night together.

228
00:10:43,343 --> 00:10:44,911
- How about a flower field?
- It's winter right now.

229
00:10:44,978 --> 00:10:47,180
Wait, how about the aquarium?

230
00:10:47,247 --> 00:10:48,348
Hey, good idea!

231
00:10:48,715 --> 00:10:49,949
What do you think, Minase?

232
00:10:50,984 --> 00:10:51,985
That sounds nice!

233
00:10:52,051 --> 00:10:53,319
- Yay!
- Yay!

234
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,088
Nice idea!

235
00:10:56,055 --> 00:10:57,557
An aquarium?

236
00:10:57,624 --> 00:10:59,692
In the dark corridor
of the aquarium...

237
00:10:59,759 --> 00:11:01,861
Your hands might overlap
one another...

238
00:11:01,928 --> 00:11:04,697
So you bring a handkerchief
to keep your palms dry.

239
00:11:04,964 --> 00:11:07,200
While the fish are dancing
in the tanks...

240
00:11:07,267 --> 00:11:10,303
You're mesmerized by them
and nearly trip.

241
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:11,905
Then, he catches you in his arms.

242
00:11:11,971 --> 00:11:13,907
The two of you look
into each other's eyes...

243
00:11:14,107 --> 00:11:16,142
And after that...

244
00:11:19,946 --> 00:11:21,548
Hey, watch the stove.
It's boiling over.

245
00:11:23,616 --> 00:11:25,418
What are you guys doing?

246
00:11:25,485 --> 00:11:27,086
What have you been doing?

247
00:11:27,787 --> 00:11:30,156
Look at your dancing, singing,
and facial expressions.

248
00:11:30,623 --> 00:11:32,492
Everything is the same.
There's no change.

249
00:11:32,926 --> 00:11:35,228
You think you can beat TORINNER
like this?Are you kidding me?

250
00:11:35,662 --> 00:11:38,097
You think this is enough
to entertain the fans?

251
00:11:38,498 --> 00:11:40,033
You make no effort to improve.

252
00:11:40,099 --> 00:11:41,267
Can you call
yourselves professionals?

253
00:11:41,768 --> 00:11:44,671
You haven't improved at all
since I first trained you.

254
00:11:45,038 --> 00:11:48,675
You're satisfied with your debut,
and then you disappear.

255
00:11:49,142 --> 00:11:50,843
It's the typical end of
a hopeless group.

256
00:11:51,811 --> 00:11:53,613
Does she have to be so harsh?

257
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:54,681
For example, Turn.

258
00:11:55,081 --> 00:11:57,617
Your dancing skills
are the best in the team.

259
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:58,952
Thank you.

260
00:11:59,018 --> 00:12:02,222
But as the main dancer
who is supposed to lead the team

261
00:12:02,322 --> 00:12:03,356
you've failed.

262
00:12:04,023 --> 00:12:05,024
Hey!

263
00:12:05,091 --> 00:12:06,993
You lack charm as a dancer.

264
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:10,797
That's why the dance doesn't have
a proper flow.

265
00:12:11,831 --> 00:12:12,832
I'm sorry.

266
00:12:13,266 --> 00:12:14,267
Next, Do-hyeok.

267
00:12:14,801 --> 00:12:17,737
Your looks are the team's strength.

268
00:12:17,804 --> 00:12:18,805
Thank you.

269
00:12:18,871 --> 00:12:21,441
But good looks are all you have.

270
00:12:22,642 --> 00:12:24,210
Your facial expressions
and dance movements are stiff.

271
00:12:24,277 --> 00:12:26,145
As a performer who should
enthrall the audience

272
00:12:26,212 --> 00:12:27,480
you've failed.

273
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:29,849
I'm sorry.

274
00:12:34,988 --> 00:12:36,256
One week.

275
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:41,728
One week later, we'll hold
a second auditionfor NAZE.

276
00:12:42,395 --> 00:12:46,099
I'll assess whether you are essential
this team or not.

277
00:12:47,166 --> 00:12:50,436
So, if you conclude
that we aren't essential...

278
00:12:50,503 --> 00:12:52,071
You'll have to leave NAZE, of course.

279
00:12:52,872 --> 00:12:56,609
Seven members are too many
to show off your individuality.

280
00:12:56,676 --> 00:12:58,244
Let's see...

281
00:12:58,845 --> 00:13:00,446
Five should be just right.

282
00:13:03,650 --> 00:13:05,118
Hey, Mr. Azuma...

283
00:13:13,993 --> 00:13:15,461
Well, we're in trouble.

284
00:13:15,662 --> 00:13:17,897
Idiot! Why are you so nonchalant?

285
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:22,035
Look, NAZE's selling point
is their friendship and teamwork.

286
00:13:22,235 --> 00:13:23,803
Why are you trying
to cause a rift between them?

287
00:13:23,870 --> 00:13:24,871
Exactly.

288
00:13:24,937 --> 00:13:27,073
There's no way
we'll remove any member.

289
00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:30,476
Mr. Azuma said he wanted
to turn NAZE into top artists.

290
00:13:30,777 --> 00:13:32,545
I'm just providing
the necessary support.

291
00:13:32,612 --> 00:13:34,714
Azuma didn't say he'd fire them!

292
00:13:34,781 --> 00:13:35,815
Ms. Nam.

293
00:13:37,684 --> 00:13:41,254
Will they be able to beat TORINNER
as they are now?

294
00:13:42,989 --> 00:13:45,224
Did you mistake the K-pop industry

295
00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:48,494
for an aquarium
full of beautiful fish?

296
00:13:49,228 --> 00:13:52,165
We're in a school of hungry sharks.

297
00:13:52,231 --> 00:13:56,135
They need to evolve continuously,
or they'll be devoured in no time.

298
00:13:57,637 --> 00:14:00,039
A second audition sounds interesting.

299
00:14:00,106 --> 00:14:03,042
I look forward to seeing
another side of them.

300
00:14:06,946 --> 00:14:11,150
You agree with every single thing
Ms. Park says.

301
00:14:15,822 --> 00:14:17,924
Will they really get rid of
two of us?

302
00:14:18,291 --> 00:14:20,893
Ms. Park said that,
so I think they'll do it.

303
00:14:22,462 --> 00:14:23,963
How can they do this?

304
00:14:25,198 --> 00:14:28,901
She said my looks are
my only strength.

305
00:14:30,837 --> 00:14:32,305
That's not true.

306
00:14:33,106 --> 00:14:34,407
Don't take it to heart, Do-hyeok.

307
00:14:35,608 --> 00:14:37,009
But at this rate...

308
00:14:45,118 --> 00:14:47,854
I think Ms. Park is right.

309
00:14:53,259 --> 00:14:57,530
We can't survive if we keep
repeating the same routine.

310
00:15:03,403 --> 00:15:08,040
I should've realized
something so important.

311
00:15:10,042 --> 00:15:11,544
I'm sorry, everyone.

312
00:15:13,346 --> 00:15:15,848
Ato, it's not your fault.
This concerns everyone.

313
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:21,521
But I also agree that
we can't continue like this.

314
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:27,326
What? So you agree
to her layoff plan?

315
00:15:28,828 --> 00:15:30,329
Then we can't stay as seven.

316
00:15:31,431 --> 00:15:33,733
- But...
- In order to survive...

317
00:15:37,170 --> 00:15:40,673
I'll fight, even against our members.

318
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:51,117
I see you're still working hard.

319
00:15:52,251 --> 00:15:55,021
How about having
some Japanese oden together?

320
00:15:55,421 --> 00:15:56,823
It's perfect for a cold day.

321
00:15:58,357 --> 00:15:59,592
Thank you.

322
00:16:01,561 --> 00:16:05,064
Are Ms. Nam and Minase okay?

323
00:16:07,433 --> 00:16:08,468
They'll be okay.

324
00:16:08,534 --> 00:16:10,770
It might have been
too harsh for them, though.

325
00:16:13,172 --> 00:16:14,640
This is my flaw.

326
00:16:16,309 --> 00:16:17,376
Same here.

327
00:16:18,177 --> 00:16:22,215
Still, there are times
when I have to treat them coldly.

328
00:16:22,281 --> 00:16:23,916
But I tend to hesitate if I'm alone

329
00:16:24,517 --> 00:16:26,285
so I appreciate your surprise attack.

330
00:16:27,687 --> 00:16:28,988
Why will you hesitate?

331
00:16:30,723 --> 00:16:31,791
In the past

332
00:16:33,559 --> 00:16:37,597
I had pushed
some talented young men too hard.

333
00:16:40,132 --> 00:16:41,167
SS.

334
00:16:43,102 --> 00:16:47,740
That's SEVEN SEAS, the group
you produced in the past, right?

335
00:16:50,176 --> 00:16:51,978
They had an audience
of 200,000 in Japan.

336
00:16:52,378 --> 00:16:53,946
Their Asia tour was successful.

337
00:16:54,413 --> 00:16:56,449
So I assumed
everything went smoothly.

338
00:16:57,083 --> 00:16:59,819
Then, I pushed them too hard.

339
00:17:00,753 --> 00:17:02,955
I kept telling them to work harder.

340
00:17:05,324 --> 00:17:07,326
I unilaterally imposed
my dream on them

341
00:17:08,194 --> 00:17:09,362
and made them suffer.

342
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:13,399
And in the end, I abandoned SS.

343
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:15,434
I gave up on everything halfway.

344
00:17:15,501 --> 00:17:18,104
Are you okay with ruining our lives?

345
00:17:20,907 --> 00:17:25,845
I had read in a gossip magazine
that you abused your power.

346
00:17:25,912 --> 00:17:28,781
That's right. Then, I was
blacklisted by the industry.

347
00:17:29,015 --> 00:17:32,318
I was told not to get involved
with them again, and I agreed.

348
00:17:32,752 --> 00:17:35,321
Because I thought it was
the best I could do to protect them.

349
00:17:36,989 --> 00:17:40,893
But SEVEN SEAS retired
right after that.

350
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:44,263
I have no idea where they are
and what they're doing now.

351
00:17:45,031 --> 00:17:46,866
I acted all cool
and talked about my dream.

352
00:17:48,234 --> 00:17:51,103
I let them choose a life that was
all about singing and dancing.

353
00:17:52,605 --> 00:17:54,674
Yet, I couldn't take responsibility
until the end.

354
00:17:59,779 --> 00:18:02,148
I was the one who ruined their lives.

355
00:18:10,156 --> 00:18:11,924
Guess I went on too long
about all that boring stuff.

356
00:18:12,558 --> 00:18:14,093
Anyway, enough about my story.

357
00:18:14,660 --> 00:18:18,097
I know you're playing the bad guy
to help NAZE grow.

358
00:18:18,898 --> 00:18:19,932
Thanks.

359
00:18:23,069 --> 00:18:24,203
You're welcome.

360
00:18:25,805 --> 00:18:27,940
Okay, it's time
for a special training session!

361
00:18:28,007 --> 00:18:31,477
Screw that second audition!

362
00:18:31,544 --> 00:18:36,282
I swear I'll make you all win
and stay here!

363
00:18:39,085 --> 00:18:40,086
What?

364
00:18:41,854 --> 00:18:44,156
The song I just played will be
your next assigned song.

365
00:18:44,457 --> 00:18:48,227
Use this song to show us
a completely new side of NAZE.

366
00:18:49,195 --> 00:18:52,164
This is the evaluation criterion
for the second audition.

367
00:18:52,231 --> 00:18:54,900
A completely new side of NAZE?

368
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:56,535
What does that mean?

369
00:18:57,770 --> 00:19:00,573
You want to survive
in the K-pop world, right?

370
00:19:02,241 --> 00:19:06,579
Then think about what you need
to improve yourself.

371
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:11,083
Line distribution, choreography,
and facial expressions.

372
00:19:11,450 --> 00:19:16,555
Think about this song from every
angle until your brain is fried.

373
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:18,391
Where's your answer?

374
00:19:19,458 --> 00:19:20,726
- I understand.
- I understand.

375
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,996
We'll have a midterm assessment
in two days.

376
00:19:24,597 --> 00:19:26,699
I expect everyone
to do their very best.

377
00:19:30,803 --> 00:19:32,772
The song Park Ji-soo brought

378
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:35,641
has a totally different style
from their debut song.

379
00:19:35,708 --> 00:19:36,742
- Are you sure about this?
- The song is good, right?

380
00:19:36,809 --> 00:19:38,811
It's perfect for their image
as their second single.

381
00:19:39,512 --> 00:19:43,983
When things go according
to her plan, I just feel like...

382
00:19:44,050 --> 00:19:45,051
Enough of that.

383
00:19:45,117 --> 00:19:48,387
Did Choi Ki-young call to protest
and tell us to give Park back?

384
00:19:48,454 --> 00:19:49,455
Not a single call.

385
00:19:49,989 --> 00:19:52,692
She did say that he was angry that
she overspent on promoting the group.

386
00:19:52,758 --> 00:19:55,161
Choi fired her. Besides,
her personality is horrible.

387
00:19:59,498 --> 00:20:00,599
How about doing this here?

388
00:20:00,666 --> 00:20:03,035
Five, six, seven, eight.

389
00:20:03,135 --> 00:20:04,970
It's the same as usual.

390
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:06,472
Make it flashier.

391
00:20:06,539 --> 00:20:08,240
We can add some steps, for example...

392
00:20:08,507 --> 00:20:13,512
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

393
00:20:13,579 --> 00:20:15,581
Movements like these
are too difficult.

394
00:20:15,648 --> 00:20:18,217
It's pointless
if we don't try something new.

395
00:20:18,284 --> 00:20:20,252
I'm telling you to face reality.

396
00:20:20,319 --> 00:20:21,721
- Hey...
- Wait...

397
00:20:22,321 --> 00:20:25,758
You two! Fighting isn't productive.

398
00:20:28,327 --> 00:20:31,597
Did you see such a lovely girl?
Did you see such...

399
00:20:31,664 --> 00:20:32,798
Hey, stop! Stop!

400
00:20:32,865 --> 00:20:34,667
Your face is totally blank.

401
00:20:34,734 --> 00:20:37,336
- You must remember to smile!
- I'm sorry.

402
00:20:37,403 --> 00:20:39,038
He won't get it
unless you give him precise advice.

403
00:20:39,105 --> 00:20:41,607
- Make Do-hyeok understand.
- But I've explained so many times!

404
00:20:41,674 --> 00:20:42,908
But he doesn't get it.

405
00:20:42,975 --> 00:20:45,111
- Calm down.
- How can I not be annoyed?

406
00:20:45,177 --> 00:20:47,947
I could be fired
if I don't practice too!

407
00:20:48,013 --> 00:20:49,448
I am sorry, Younki.

408
00:20:57,823 --> 00:20:59,859
It hurts! Don't bump into me!

409
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:01,927
What? It's your fault
for being there.

410
00:21:01,994 --> 00:21:03,662
Don't be ridiculous!

411
00:21:03,729 --> 00:21:04,964
Hey, keep it down!

412
00:21:05,197 --> 00:21:06,499
You'll get injured!

413
00:21:06,565 --> 00:21:07,833
Watch out!

414
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:10,269
Fight outside if you want to fight!

415
00:21:10,336 --> 00:21:12,638
Now, let's begin
the midterm evaluation.

416
00:21:13,939 --> 00:21:15,040
- Yes, ma'am.
- Yes, ma'am.

417
00:21:20,412 --> 00:21:21,447
Play the song.

418
00:21:43,135 --> 00:21:44,270
Is this a joke?

419
00:21:45,704 --> 00:21:50,075
You're only trying your best
to dance and sing.

420
00:21:50,476 --> 00:21:53,879
You don't understand what is
necessary to perform this song.

421
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:58,984
I can't believe you think you can
perform like this in front of people.

422
00:22:05,291 --> 00:22:06,325
In the end

423
00:22:07,426 --> 00:22:09,128
losers can never change.

424
00:22:18,237 --> 00:22:20,673
This is only the midterm evaluation.

425
00:22:20,739 --> 00:22:21,740
Let's do our best
during the real thing.

426
00:22:21,807 --> 00:22:22,875
Mr. Azuma.

427
00:22:24,610 --> 00:22:27,913
What will happen
if we fail next time?

428
00:22:29,949 --> 00:22:32,551
Is it really over for us,
just as Ms. Park said?

429
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:35,921
Yeah.

430
00:22:37,823 --> 00:22:39,658
If you can't discover
your new potential

431
00:22:39,725 --> 00:22:41,727
you're better off
considering a different career.

432
00:22:42,294 --> 00:22:43,596
I feel the same.

433
00:22:54,940 --> 00:22:57,276
It's natural to feel bewildered
when someone tells you

434
00:22:57,476 --> 00:22:59,278
they'll remove members from the team.

435
00:22:59,345 --> 00:23:01,480
You couldn't focus on practicing.

436
00:23:02,448 --> 00:23:03,682
It can't be helped.

437
00:23:06,418 --> 00:23:08,020
That's exactly why we failed.

438
00:23:09,255 --> 00:23:10,256
What?

439
00:23:10,990 --> 00:23:12,424
Times like these

440
00:23:13,459 --> 00:23:15,561
are when we need
to practice as hard as we can.

441
00:23:17,529 --> 00:23:19,198
But we aren't united.

442
00:23:20,466 --> 00:23:23,669
There's no way
we can perform well like this!

443
00:23:23,736 --> 00:23:25,704
- You're one to talk!
- Stop it.

444
00:23:25,771 --> 00:23:29,174
Seriously. It'll be over for us
if this continues.

445
00:23:29,241 --> 00:23:32,044
But it's not like
we've been slacking off.

446
00:23:32,678 --> 00:23:34,246
We've been working pretty hard.

447
00:23:40,452 --> 00:23:41,487
I'm quitting.

448
00:23:44,156 --> 00:23:45,791
What are you saying, Do-hyeok?

449
00:23:45,858 --> 00:23:50,329
Neither my dancing nor my singing
skills are useful to the team.

450
00:23:53,032 --> 00:23:55,901
It'll be better for NAZE if I leave.

451
00:23:55,968 --> 00:23:57,002
Don't think like that--

452
00:23:57,069 --> 00:23:59,305
I'm sick of us fighting!

453
00:24:02,975 --> 00:24:04,743
We've been doing this together

454
00:24:05,811 --> 00:24:08,314
and I wanted you guys
to always get along.

455
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:11,817
But I couldn't do anything.

456
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:16,121
So I'm going to quit!

457
00:24:18,424 --> 00:24:19,725
That's the only thing I can do

458
00:24:20,859 --> 00:24:23,128
to make myself useful to everyone.

459
00:24:33,839 --> 00:24:36,842
I love NAZE.

460
00:24:37,643 --> 00:24:39,144
I love you guys too.

461
00:24:40,946 --> 00:24:41,947
That's why

462
00:24:43,115 --> 00:24:46,452
I want the seven of us
to become top artists together.

463
00:24:50,522 --> 00:24:54,059
I want us to beat TORINNER
and become number one.

464
00:24:56,295 --> 00:24:57,296
What about you guys?

465
00:24:59,098 --> 00:25:02,234
I feel the same, but...

466
00:25:02,735 --> 00:25:03,769
Me too.

467
00:25:04,436 --> 00:25:07,373
But they'll eliminate two of us.

468
00:25:08,707 --> 00:25:09,742
Yeah.

469
00:25:10,876 --> 00:25:12,111
But first of all

470
00:25:13,045 --> 00:25:17,082
what should we do
the best version of NAZE?

471
00:25:17,583 --> 00:25:20,219
Why don't we
think through it once more?

472
00:25:21,387 --> 00:25:22,588
I'm sure

473
00:25:23,389 --> 00:25:25,257
it's something
that only we can come up with.

474
00:25:26,492 --> 00:25:30,729
Because all seven of us

475
00:25:32,197 --> 00:25:33,532
made NAZE.

476
00:25:47,112 --> 00:25:49,748
You're way too passionate, as always.

477
00:25:52,551 --> 00:25:54,486
We don't need to change everything.

478
00:25:55,020 --> 00:25:57,756
We have tons of strengths, too.

479
00:26:00,225 --> 00:26:01,460
That's right.

480
00:26:02,361 --> 00:26:03,529
Ato's singing.

481
00:26:04,063 --> 00:26:05,264
Yuya's breakdance.

482
00:26:05,531 --> 00:26:06,665
Kun's rap.

483
00:26:07,166 --> 00:26:09,535
And Do-hyeok's amazing visuals.

484
00:26:09,902 --> 00:26:12,938
But she said
my good looks were all I had.

485
00:26:13,138 --> 00:26:14,840
That's not true!

486
00:26:15,674 --> 00:26:18,644
Our youngest member's charm
is our team's strength!

487
00:26:22,981 --> 00:26:25,751
Wait, what about me?
There's nothing about me?

488
00:26:26,018 --> 00:26:27,753
Well...

489
00:26:30,189 --> 00:26:31,190
Seriously? Nothing?

490
00:26:31,957 --> 00:26:32,991
We're kidding!

491
00:26:33,058 --> 00:26:36,095
Kaisei, you're the best
at being calm and mature!

492
00:26:36,161 --> 00:26:37,863
That just means I'm old!

493
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:42,101
Join us, Minase.

494
00:26:42,234 --> 00:26:43,235
Really?

495
00:26:44,002 --> 00:26:45,070
Got it.

496
00:26:46,138 --> 00:26:47,139
Then...

497
00:26:48,373 --> 00:26:49,575
Let's do our best.

498
00:26:54,012 --> 00:26:55,013
One, two...

499
00:26:55,681 --> 00:26:56,949
- NAZE!
- NAZE!

500
00:26:57,015 --> 00:26:59,785
- Let's do our best!
- Let's go!

501
00:26:59,852 --> 00:27:01,587
Yay!

502
00:27:03,055 --> 00:27:04,056
It's from Ryo!

503
00:27:04,590 --> 00:27:07,392
Sorry, we've been having lessons
from morning to night every day

504
00:27:07,459 --> 00:27:08,627
without any break.

505
00:27:09,228 --> 00:27:10,262
It's killing me.

506
00:27:10,629 --> 00:27:11,864
Did something happen, Yuya?

507
00:27:12,197 --> 00:27:15,701
Actually,
we're having a tough time too.

508
00:27:16,602 --> 00:27:20,038
I looked up on social media,
and I found two of our strengths.

509
00:27:20,105 --> 00:27:21,106
Two?

510
00:27:21,173 --> 00:27:22,174
People say we look close

511
00:27:22,407 --> 00:27:23,709
and seem like naive, innocent boys.

512
00:27:24,109 --> 00:27:25,777
So we can either double down
on that impression

513
00:27:25,878 --> 00:27:27,546
or go in a different direction.

514
00:27:27,613 --> 00:27:29,414
A different direction?

515
00:27:29,581 --> 00:27:31,016
It's difficult.

516
00:27:31,517 --> 00:27:34,286
Guys, I just talked to my Ryo.

517
00:27:34,353 --> 00:27:35,988
Really? What did Ryo say?

518
00:27:36,054 --> 00:27:39,291
He said we could try something
a bit more mature.

519
